played a key role in the smallpox vaccination campaigns in Peru; and José Manuel Valdés, a multifaceted writer who became the first and only person of black ancestry to become a chief medical officer in Spanish America. By carefully documenting their actions and writings, The Black Doctors of Colonial Lima illustrates how medicine and its related fields became areas in which the descendants of slaves found opportunities for social and political advancement, and a platform from which to engage in provocative dialogue with Enlightenment thought and social revolution.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBlack people in medicinezPeruzLimaxSocial conditionsy18th century. 0aBlack people in medicinezPeruzLimaxSocial conditionsy19th century. 0aBlack peoplezPeruzLimaxSocial conditionsy18th century. 0aBlack peoplezPeruzLimaxSocial conditionsy19th century. 0aBlacksxHistoryxPeruxLima. 0aBlackszPeruzLimaxHistory. 0aMedical writingxSocial aspectsxHistoryxPeruxLima. 0aMedical writingxSocial aspectszPeruzLimaxHistory. 0aMedicinexHistoryy18th century. 0aPhysiciansxHistoryxPeruxLima. 0aPhysicianszPeruzLimavBiography. 0aPhysicianszPeruzLimaxHistory. 0aRacexSocial aspectsxHistoryxPeruxLima. 0aRacexSocial aspectszPeruzLimaxHistory. 0aSciencexSocial aspectsxHistoryxPeruxLima. 0aSciencexSocial aspectszPeruzLimaxHistory. 0aSocial medicinexHistoryxPeruxLima. 0aSocial medicinezPeruzLimaxHistory. 0aSurgeonsxHistoryxPeruxLima. 0aSurgeonszPeruzLimavBiography. 0aSurgeonszPeruzLimaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / South America.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709740uhttps:/